                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14477497" author="paulk" created="Sat, 29 Sep 2007 02:14:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This isn&apos;t a bug but current behaviour. The all jar doesn&apos;t include the commons-cli which you need. You may ask for a feature enhancement if you want a jar merging commons-cli.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14463305" author="jede" created="Sun, 14 Oct 2007 13:35:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have the same problem. It&apos;s really annoying to include the commons-cli.jar everytime just for the groovyc Ant task. The idea of the  groovy-all-1.1-rc-1.jar is to include all dependencies. It contains the groovyc Ant task  but not the required commons-cli.jar. It would be great when it could be included, hopefully in the 1.1 release.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
Stefan&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14463210" author="guillaume" created="Sun, 14 Oct 2007 15:51:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We should probably include commons-cli in the all jar.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14477522" author="paulk" created="Wed, 17 Oct 2007 00:17:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in head&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14463589" author="russel" created="Wed, 14 Nov 2007 05:00:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This change has broken Grails.  cf. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2295&quot; title=&quot;Groovy embeddable JAR contains outdated version of Commons CLI causing problems with Gant/Grails&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-2295&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-2295&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  The problem is to do with Gant and how to compile it for use with groovy-all instead of groovy + commons-cli.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14477577" author="paulk" created="Wed, 14 Nov 2007 06:37:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A fix has been proposed for the issue Russel mentioned which should mean the solution to this issue will not be impacted.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14463535" author="russel" created="Wed, 14 Nov 2007 09:47:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Which is why I didn&apos;t reopen the issue &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I put the marker here more to ensure we had a proper connection between issues for documentation purposes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
